==English==

===Etymology===
The term has arisen from the conflicts in the 20th century [[Balkans]]. 

===Noun===
'''Balkanization''' (alternate UK spelling: '''Balkanisation''')
#A geopolitical term to describe the [[fragment]]ation of a [[region]] into many smaller regions that are often [[hostile]] or non-cooperative with each other.
#''(colloquial)'': Any [[disintegration]] process, such as the of Internet being divided into [[separate]] enclaves.

